summary:
Passionate data professional with experience in different roles within Analytics & Machine Learning. I have an international background and a proven track record using data pipelines, visualizations, statistics, and predictive algorithms to derive actionable insight. 

I am a self-starter and avid learner. I bring added value through my technical skills, creative problem-solving, can-do attitude, and drive to improve each day. I am motivated by new, complex challenges and thrive in a team setting. 

Competencies: 
- Algorithms: Linear & Logistic Regression, Random Forest, Gradient Boosting, KNN, Naïve Bayes, Support Vector Machines, k-Means, Hierarchical Clustering, NLP, Neural Networks
- Languages/Tools: Python, SQL, Spark & SparkML, Bash, R, Docker, AWS, Git, MATLAB, SPSS, HPC, Slurm, RDBMS, ETL, Hypothesis Testing, A/B Testing
- Packages: NumPy, SciPy, Pandas, Scikit-Learn, PySpark, PyTorch, NLTK, Gensim, SpaCy, TextBlob, Tidyverse, BeautifulSoup, Selenium
- Visualization tools: Tableau, RShiny, Seaborn, Matplotlib, Plotly, Dash, ggplot, Excel

awards.title: John H. Moe Award Nominee for Best Basic Science Poster
awards.description:
The Moe award is given to the best basic science poster or e-poster at the SRS Annual Meeting.

Neilsen D, Gehrchen M, Dahl B, Harris JA, Gudipally M, Jenkins S, Wu A, Bucklen B. "Where Does Rod Strain Migrate? An In Vitro Cadaveric Study of Four-Rod Techniques Used to Alleviate Rod Fracture in Adult Spinal Deformity Correction." Scoliosis Research Society, 2015. Minnesota, MN. Electronic Poster.

awards.title: Russel W. Hibbs Basic Research Award Nominee
awards.description:
The Russell A. Hibbs awards are given to both the best basic science and clinical papers presented at the SRS Annual Meeting.

64.	Neilsen D, Gehrchen M, Dahl B, Harris JA, Gudipally M, Jenkins S, Wu A, Bucklen B. "Evaluation of Spinal Reconstruction following Pedicle Subtraction Osteotomy: Effect of Four Rods and Interbody Support on Resulting Rod Strain". Scoliosis Research Society, 2015. Minnesota, MN. Podium Presentation.

awards.title: Thomas Whitecloud Basic Science Nominee
awards.description:
Nominees for the Whitecloud Best Basic Science and Clinical awards are selected by the IMAST Committee from the submitted 2019 abstracts for the IMAST and the SRS Annual Meeting.

Neilsen D, Gehrchen M, Dahl B, Harris JA, Gudipally M, Jenkins S, Wu A, Bucklen B. "Does Anterior Column Support Following a Pedicle Subtraction Osteotomy Reduce Rod Strain? An In Vitro Biomechanical Investigation." International Meeting on Advanced Spine Techniques, 2015. Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. Podium presentation.
